sec.p:
For DOX conjugation onto the S1 surface, a reported procedure48,63 with slight modification was adopted. In brief, S1 was dispersed into an aqueous solution of 60 μL of 1-(3-dimethylaminopropyl)-N′-Ethyl carbodiimide hydrochloride/ N-hydroxysuccinimide (EDC/C4H5NO3) (80/20 mg ratio). Then 3 mL of DOX (18.0 mM) was added to this solution and stirred for three hours. Ultrafiltration (Ultrafree-MC VV Filter, Merck, Germany) was used for separation of DOX conjugated nanoparticles. The DOX loading efficiency was calculated by UV-Vis measurements at 480 nm from the difference between the DOX conjugated to the S1 and the amount of unbound DOX in the supernatant using following equation:1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
